Class GeneralTreeTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • GeneralTreeTest

  • public class GeneralTreeTest
extends java.lang.Object
    Test class for General Tree that is extended from Binary Tree This class controls all of the public methods and their possible outcomes
    Author:
    Yasir

      void addSuccessful()
      Creates a general tree and tries to add an element that has a parent in the created tree Expected result is a successful addition
      void addUnsuccessful()
      Creates a general tree and tries to add an element that hasn't got the given parent in the created tree Expected result is an unsuccessful addition
      void levelOrderSearchTest()
      Creates a general tree with 7 nodes and tries to search an item in this tree using level order traversal's search Checks for the children of the found node to verify that the search method is working
      void levelOrderTraverseTest()
      Creates a general tree with 7 nodes and tries to traverse this tree level order and compares the result of traversal with expected output

      void postOrderTraverseTest()
      Creates a general tree with 7 nodes and tries to traverse this tree post order and compares the result of traversal with expected output
      void preOrderTraverseTest()
      Creates a general tree with 7 nodes and tries to traverse this tree pre order and compares the result of traversal with expected output
